    "scenario": {
      "en": "A 58-year-old man with hypertension and smoking history presents with severe crushing chest pain radiating to his left arm for 2 hours. He is diaphoretic and nauseated. ECG shows ST elevation in leads II, III, and aVF. Troponin is elevated.",
